Load up the tidyverse

The following code will load up the tidyverse package, which is a package of packages.

library(tidyverse)

Load the data

This will load a data frame from a URL.

weight_df <- read_csv("data/weight.csv")

This data frame has 6068 observations and 8 variables.

A scatterplot

The following scatterplot will show each persons weight as function of their height, and show the lines of best fit.
